        <figure id="f0502A52" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0023945.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                     scalefitheight="392px"/>
            <caption>Figure 1. Dana Model S110 Wheel Differential Assembly, Disassembled View</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Differential bearing adjusting ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Differential side bearing cup</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Differential side bearing cone</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Differential case (conventional differential)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Differential side gear thrust washer</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Differential side gear (conventional differential)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Differential pinion shaft</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Differential pinion gear</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Differential pinion thrust washer</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Differential pinion shaft pin (conventional differential)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Differential ring gear</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Differential ring gear bolt</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Differential side bearing cone</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Differential side bearing cup</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Differential bearing adjusting ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Anti-lock speed sensor ring</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mount the carrier housing in a suitable repair stand.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a53" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0023951.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>If reusing the differential ring gear and pinion, measure and record the backlash before
                    disassembly. Assembling the differential ring gear and pinion to the recorded backlash will match
                    the established wear patterns. Hand-rolled patterns will cover less area than the established
                    patterns.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure and record the differential ring gear and pinion backlash.</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Check the backlash in 4 equally spaced positions around the differential ring gear.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>The tooth contact pattern can move only by adjusting backlash. The tooth contact pattern can
                        move only in the direction of heel-to-toe and toe-to-heel. Depth of the tooth contact pattern is
                        not adjustable. Contact Spicer Service at 1-800-666-8688 for assistance if you are unable to
                        establish an acceptable tooth contact pattern within the limits of backlash.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a54" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1916A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the rear anti-lock brake sensor.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a55" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1917A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the adjusting ring cotter pins.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a56" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0023952.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen, but do not remove, the 6 differential bearing cap bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a57" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1920A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Relieve the bearing preload.</para>
            <para>&#8226; Loosen each differential bearing adjusting ring.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a58" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1921A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the differential bearing cap bolts, differential bearing caps and adjusting rings.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a59" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1920A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Carefully lift the differential subassembly out of the carrier.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the differential side bearing surfaces for pitting, wear and overheating.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a60" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1929A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using the special tools, remove the differential side bearings if worn or damaged.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a61" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024108.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 12 differential ring gear bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a62" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0062219.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the differential assembly in a suitable press supported on the differential ring
                gear.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a63" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0062238.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>The differential case will fall after separation. Support the case so it will not result in damage
                    to the component or equipment. Failure to follow these instructions can result in personal injury.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>It should not require more than 3 tons of press load to separate the ring gear from the
                    differential case.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Do not bend the differential pinion cross shaft.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The press arbor will push on the differential pinion cross shaft to separate the ring gear
                half of the differential from the cross shaft half of the assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a64" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0062237.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Discard the anti-lock speed sensor ring if separating it from the ring gear side case half.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If necessary, remove the anti-lock speed sensor ring.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a65" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0062213.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Alkaline cleaning solutions will damage machine surfaces. Use only emulsion cleaners or
                    petroleum-based cleaning solvents.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Use soft, clean, lintless towels to dry the components.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Never spin-dry bearings with compressed air. This will damage the mating surfaces due to a lack of
                    lubrication.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>After drying, lightly coat the components with rust inhibitor or clean lubricant to prevent damage
                    from corrosion. Wrap all components that are going to be in storage for a prolonged period in wax
                    paper.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>For Truetrac&#174; differentials, submerge the entire differential assembly in a suitable solvent
                    to wash away contaminants from within the housing.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean and dry the components.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The Truetrac&#174; differential assembly is non-repairable. Discard the entire assembly if
                it is worn or damaged.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a66" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figDE3/DE3043A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With a conventional differential, lift out the side gear.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a67" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0062241.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the differential pinion cross shaft lock pin.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a68" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0062242.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Discard all gears in sets if one or more sustains wear or damage.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the pinion cross shaft.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a69" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0062245.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the inner side gear and thrust washer.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a70" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0062246.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
